CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 12, 1964, pg. 14 reads: "Queen For A Day - Miss Georgiana Hill (seated) reigned as queen of the unique program sponsored by the Harriet Tubman Guild, at the downtown YWCA, last Friday evening. The queen represented the Efficiency Chapter, which rallied to the tune of $200 to give her first place.  Runners-up were (left to right) Mrs. Louise Smith of the Hallie Q. Brown Chapter, second place; Mrs. Noreen Kenda, Triboro Chapter, third, and Mrs. Mildred Connor, representing the Founders Chapter.  All of them reported $100 or more. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of man placing crown on head of Georgiana Hill, standing between seven women including on left: three unknown women, and Louise Smith; on right: Noreen Kenda, Mildred Connor, and unknown woman, posed on stage during Harriet Tubman Guild event, downtown YWCA
